#3monthsold on 12/22, just in time for the holidays! (The #angelcado onesie seemed appropriate for Christmas-thanks @marisacatalina for these cute matching outfits!). Our #babycado loves the lights on our tree, crinkly toys, attempting to roll over (doesn't quite do it yet), laughing, and figuring out what she can do with her hands, including grabbing mommy's hair and grabbing/trying to eat her clothes! She doesn't always like to nap, but we're so grateful to be able to celebrate her this holiday season! #LiliaElaina #CoraMarin #threemonthsold #babymilestones @reedjeremy #holyguacamole

Merry Christmas, Happy #Christmakkah / Hanukkah and Happy Holidays from my (#Tedlasso obsessed) family to yours! It's still hard to believe sometimes that this beautiful new baby and family are mine, and I'm so grateful. If you are struggling this holiday season, I'm also sending love your way. I am also grateful to be back at weddings since October and to have captured so many recent beautiful family/holiday scenes...I promise to post more of that painting content soon! For now, I hope everyone is enjoying some relaxing time at home and/or with loved ones. #merrychristmas #happyholidays #christmas2022 #christmaspajamas #familypajamas #familyportrait #LiliaElaina #CoraMarin @reedjeremy

I'm #fourmonthsold today on this cloudy day, and trying (and sometimes succeeding!) to roll over and grab and suck on ALL the avocados (and some other things too, like mommy's hair and earrings, and my clothing). I'm very chatty, giggly and silly just like my big sister...and I'll probably laugh if you kiss/blow raspberries on my tummy. Especially when I'm well fed and well rested (but I'm always hungry these days!!). I love being on the move in my play gym and stroller and don't like sitting still. Thanks Auntie @tamarings for this new avocado toy--it's the best! #LiliaElaina #4monthsold #babycado #babymilestones

Happy 5 months, #babycado Lilia! You don't hate tummy time as much these days, tried your first taste of avocado (didn't like it as much as mom and dad do, but we're working on it!) and are almost sitting up on your own! You have totally won over our hearts this Valentine's Day, especially your big sister's, who also likes taking your picture and will do anything to make you smile (but luckily, you're smiling most of the time, and your fussiness is often cured simply by putting on some music, which you love!) You also love visiting new places, meeting new people and observing the world around you, and we are thrilled to be able to share our world with you! #LiliaElaina #CoraMarin #5monthsold #babymilestones #sisterlove

#WeddingWednesday: what's your preferred "recipe" for a live painting? I'd argue that you need everything here!! (And if there's a cute dog named Gatsby, that's an added bonus!) Catching up on posting the progress on my #liveeventpainting of Michael and Michael's gorgeous #oceanside #weddingceremony at @thepiermont on 2/3/23. #flashbackfriday #fbf: I've gotten several recent inquiries about whether I can paint a #churchceremony #weddingceremony and the answer is, of course, YES! I love capturing gorgeous #cathedral backgrounds and the most important religious traditions of your wedding. The church just needs to allow me to come early enough to set up and stay late enough to clean up after the ceremony and ideally provide a table, chair and outlet in a space with a decent view of the #altar--it's ideal if I can have a few hours before or after the ceremony to paint as much of the background as possible onsite, but I can finish lot of the painting at your reception space afterwards and/or in my studio! Here is a finished 24"x30" #liveeventpainting from February 2022, painted onsite at St. Mary Coptic Orthodox Church East Brunswick, NJ and continued at the party and with studio touchups. Includes some of the congregation, #weddingparty, and family. My goal is to share at least one of my finished 2022 paintings I haven't shared yet per week. What would you like to see next? 

#liveeventpainter #eventpaintingbykatherine #weddingpainter #weddingpainting #njwedding #copticorthodox #copticorthodoxwedding

A sneak preview of last night's #liveeventpainting at the always gorgeous @theparksavoy - and I'll be back next week too! 6 months with our #tinymiracle (Posting a day late). She's changed so much in just the past month, working on sitting up, splashing in the bath, trying all of mommy and daddy's favorite foods (including avocado (duh!) and she especially loves/so far is not allergic to peanut and almond butter), swinging at the playground, carefully scrutinizing every toy (favorites include anything with tags, mommy's phone, squooshmallows, and baby wipe packets!) and sharing inside jokes with big sis, who never fails to get a smile these days. We're having so much fun getting to know this #babycado! Onesie by @cozywarriororg.  #LiliaElaina #coramarin #sixmonthsold #halfbirthday #rainbowbaby #CHEEKS

#flashbackfriday #fbf: do you have both a lot of people, and a lot of special details you'd like included in your painting? My "Museum Package" ensures that not only all the incredible decor will be captured onsite, but there will be time to touch up the most important people in the studio afterwards. I'll also find a way to fit everything in to the composition - not just your #centerpieces and #weddingcake but things like #dancingonclouds, #monogram, #dais display, #tablescapes. So your unique vision for your #weddingdecor can live on long past the #weddingday! Venue: @southgatemanor, DJ: @eclipseeventsnj  
Photographer: @premierdigitalweddings  
Event Styling/Decor: @sbeventstyling (using flowers from @bklynbloom)

#7monthsold on #EarthDay, 4/22/23! Lilia wants everyone to know that she loves planet earth and all the natural wonders it has to offer, and she should know because in the past month she's experienced her first sunrise, swim in the ocean, cherry blossoms, and even underground cenote cave! She really hopes all of this will still be around when she and her sister grow up, and that everyone in her parents' and grandparents' generation will do their part to help. Also, a new favorite activity is trying to get toys that are just out of reach--perhaps a good metaphor for our efforts to combat our current climate crisis. If she refuses to give up, so must we-because our children's future depends on it! #LiliaElaina #savesomeplanetforme 
#earthday2023 @reedjeremy

I have started a new account, @katherinegressel_curator, dedicated to my work as contemporary curator at @oldstonehousebklyn and as an independent curator of site-specific/public/participatory art with an impact, in other alternative spaces. Please give it a follow especially if you'd like to collaborate with me in the future! 

I'm excited to share the info about my latest curatorial project:

 Mother Nature/Human Nurture
Opens Thurs April 27, 6-8pm

Mother Nature/Human Nurture features artists Pamella Allen, Qiana Mestrich and Dara Oshin, whose artwork explores themes of nature, nurture, life cycles and caretaking for ourselves, our loved ones and the Earth. Curated in collaboration by Katherine Gressel and Grace Freedman of Why Not Art, the show is presented at The Old Stone House, 336 Third St, Brooklyn, NY 11215.

Happy Mother's Day from my family to yours! While I think mothers have one of the hardest and most important jobs and deserve to be celebrated not just today but every day, I know this day can be tough for many people. It's also a difficult (and often scary) time to be a mother in this country (support @momsdemand and get cute matching tees like ours!!). But I'm so grateful for both my own mom and the two incredible girls who made me one, and to have been able to spend my first #mothersday as a mom of two with my whole family in the neighborhood I grew up in, complete with fish tacos, flowers and playgrounds in @riversideparknyc. Sending love to all the other moms out there, and especially to people still hoping to become moms or missing their own moms. ❤️❤️ #mothersday2023 #family #onetoughmother

Happy #fathersday! As some of you may know, I'm passionate about supporting my fellow artist moms and working moms. But I feel like we don't talk enough about the important role dads can-and should!-play as caregivers (and of course some kids are raised only by dads!). I'm so lucky that both my husband @reedjeremy and my own dad have never seen parenting, or caring for aging parents/partners, as "women's work" by default. If I didn't have such a supportive father growing up and competent, loving, equal partner in raising my two girls, I wouldn't be doing nearly as much in my creative and professional life. I also thank them both for being completely on board with everything we went through to have baby number 2 last year. Let's start including dads too in conversations about work/life balance, fertility and reproductive rights, and the stresses of and support needed for caregiving. Hope everyone took the time today to acknowledge the dads in their lives who are truly "doing it all" and making it possible for us moms to do so as well. And as always, I'm sending love to anyone who has lost/is missing a father, still hoping to become one, or for whom this day is difficult for any other reason. ❤️❤️❤️ #happyfathersday #CoraMarin #LiliaElaina #fathersday2023 #familyphotography #ilovemydaddy

Cheers to 9 years, @reedjeremy!! Partying with you looks a little different these days, but we're making sure our children follow in our footsteps of appreciating the fun and goofy parts of life. This includes flashy disco dancing swag, folk music singalongs (thanks as always to the amazing @ediecarey for performing at our wedding), and tasty drinks (yes, I did dress Lilia today in a onesie referencing the drink I ordered on our very first date, but we had better options at our actual wedding, lol!). So far, raising a family with you has been even more fun than our wedding, which was hard to top. I love you!! Wedding photos: @sarahhamptonphoto; venue: @mountgulian_weddings

(Unfortunately this posted without the music and I don't have time to remake it so you'll have to use your imagination and I hope you'll still show it some love!! ❤️) Throwback to last Thursday's amazing wedding at @bournemansion! Hope everyone had a "#happyfourth! Each year on this day, I like to reflect on the values upon which America was founded, and celebrate everyone who's working to get us closer to a place of true freedom and equality.  One of my passions is organizing exhibits and programs with other artists and curators whose work addresses social justice and American history, so I'm excited to be involved with several shows later in the summer and fall at @oldstonehousebklyn addressing these topics. Once again these include "Family Ties," curated by @jeremynative of @mashousestudio, inviting BIPOC artists to reflect on their own experiences with family and connect with the stories and experiences of others; and "Picturing the Constitution," inviting artists to respond to an aspect of the US Constitution, including its amendments and interpretations by the Supreme Court and various governing bodies throughout history, and reflect on the extent to which these founding documents still serve us (equitably). More info on all of this to come, but for now I'm grateful to have had a few days off this long weekend with my own family after a very busy June. Happy summer!

What a great night last night painting at the 50th anniversary fundraiser for the JDRF type 1 diabetes research foundation (@jdrfhq)! (On #worlddiabetesday) I was hired to paint the #cocktailhour at the fabulous @casaciprianinyc while guests watched, and the painting was then auctioned off to the highest bidder. I'm honored to have been selected for this and excited to have helped support a great cause--I have several close family members and friends impacted by type 1 diabetes and loved learning about the important work this organization is doing. Visit their page to make a donation or learn how you can get involved! 

I also enjoyed this because while I love weddings and they are my bread and butter, it's always refreshing to paint something a little different, especially where the organization didn't give me any specific guests to  highlight and just had me capture the atmosphere, decor and general crowd rather than a single staged moment. This is how I originally approached #liveeventpainting when I first started and I still believe in doing as much painting  directly from life, and from crowds in motion, as possible to capture the real energy of a party! Instead of working from a photo I was able to paint many of these people as they were milling about in front of me, which was a lot of fun. At the same time I couldn't resist at least referencing a few of the event VIPs who gave speeches, including host @vanessawilliamsofficial! 
22"x28" canvas completed onsite. 

Feel free to approach me for your special fundraiser or corporate event (especially if it's also 17 min from home lol).

#throwbackthursday #tbt to almost two weeks ago-still can't get over this amazing #weddingreception I had the privilege of painting at the gorgeous @tanqueverderanchweddings in the #tucson Arizona area! At first I was a little nervous that I'd taken on too much of a challenge with this painting composition and the 24"x36" canvas definitely took me the entire 6 hour party and then some completion time at my hotel. But it was so hard to leave anything out especially since the couple was crazy about both their #barnwedding reception venue architecture and the incredible #arizonadesert landscape right outside (which they requested I capture at #goldenhour.) Also, they have a large family and the most adorable dog and I was able to incorporate everyone plus some  unique cactus-themed decor details that really made this event stand out. I'm excited by how it all came together in the end and always love the challenge of putting together ALL your favorite components of your wedding (you don't have to pick just one!) Thanks again to Nicole and Jordan for a wonderful experience with my first #arizonawedding!
